          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-56d78663ad8e8944",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "What is a high-interest savings account (HISA)?\nA high-interest savings account (HISA) , also known as a high-yield savings account, is a type of bank account that offers interest rates that are above and beyond what you'd typically find with traditional savings accounts. Commonly available at major banks, credit unions and digital banks in Canada, these accounts aim to motivate individuals to grow their savings by offering competitive interest rates.\nWhat is a Premium Rate Savings Account? A Premium Rate Savings Account functions like a regular savings account where you can store your money and earn interest, but with added perks. BMO\u2019s Premium Rate Savings Account is a savings option that offers you the flexibility and convenience, including access to your money whenever you need it. It can be paired with any BMO chequing account, so you only pay one monthly account fee.",
